Properties of the predicted proteins encoded by the eight segments of RbtOV are summarized in Table 1
. The size order of the eight segments, based on total nucleotide length, was as follows: PB2, PB1, NP, PA, NA, HA, NS1/NEP, and M1/M2. This size order is similar to that of ISAV. However, compared to FLUAV and influenza B virus (FLUBV), ISAV has a fusion protein (F) instead of a neuraminidase and the hemagglutinin has esterase activity (HE), features which have not been ascertained for RbtOV (Table 2
). The segment encoding the NP of isolate RbtOV and ISAV was larger than the segment encoding the PA, which is not the case for FLUAV or FLUBV. Also, the sizes of RbtOV segments 7 and 8 were reversed with respect to their orthologs in FLUAV or FLUBV (Table 2).
